This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new architecture for neural networks that is based on sparsity and investigates the accuracy and training speed of the models. It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with neural networks and their topologies. Additionally, it could be categorized as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as neural networks are a fundamental tool in AI research. The paper also mentions experiments with image data, which suggests it could be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the properties of graph topologies, which could make it relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
